div1.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
In the Matter of the Application of Chin Quock Way for a Writ of Habeas Corpus ) No.2971 ORDER DISMISSING WRIT.

The above entitled matter having come regularly on for hearing on the 26th day of April, 1914, on the Petition for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, the Writ of Habeas Corpus,and respondent's return thereto, and the Court having heard the arguments ofcounsel and being fully advised in the premises, and having filed a written opinion herein;
IT IS HEREBY ORDERED, that said Writ be, and the same is hereby dismissed, and the petitioner remanded to the custody of the Commissioner of Immigration.
div1.ab: Jeremiah Neterer United States District Judge
div1.p: To the entry of the above order the petitioner excepts, which exception is hereby allowed.
Jeremiah Neterer United States District Judge
IN THE SUPERIOR COURT STATE OF WASHINGTON KING COUNTY
In the Matter of the Application of CHIN QUOCK WAH, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. Plaintiff vs. Defendant
PETITION FOR, AND ORDER ALLOWING, APPEAL
BEELER & SULLIVAN LAWYERS 510-11 WHITE BUILDING SEATTLE, WASH.
FILED IN THE U. S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, JUN101915
